meanings.definition: Supplying an excessive amount of something.
meanings.sent1: The oversupping store had shelves overflowing with goods.
meanings.sent2: The oversupping market flooded the town with unnecessary products.
meanings.sent3: The oversupping party had more snacks than guests!
meanings.sent4: Her oversupping generosity knew no bounds.
meanings.sent5: The oversupping rain caused flooding in the streets.

meanings.definition: Exceeding the normal or desired level of supply.
meanings.sent1: The oversupping company struggled to sell their surplus products.
meanings.sent2: The oversupping inventory led to storage issues.
meanings.sent3: The oversupping garden produced more vegetables than they could eat.
meanings.sent4: His oversupping enthusiasm for the project was contagious.
meanings.sent5: The oversupping traffic jam caused delays for hours.
